VK. Saraswati Vasudev began her veena recital with a brisk Sahana varnam, she played Bhajamanasa (Bahudari) and Saraswathinamostute (Saraswathi) before rendering a niceaalapanaof Malayamarutham at Kalabharati in Visakhapatnam.She played Manasayetulortune in it with swaram. Then after playing Adugatarama (Manoranjani), she evocatively rendered Paridaanamitchithe (Bilhari) with eruditely structuredaalapanaandswaramin the two tempos.Playing Aadamodigalada (Chaarukesi) prefixed with elaborateaalapanaand rahmakadiginapaadamu (Mukhari) with brief but beautifulaalapanaandswaramnext, she seemed to have got perfectly set for aesthetically showcasing evenly balanced ambidexterity in full measure. The Maaravairi (Naasikabhushani) next, was replete with scholarly expression of manodharma by way ofaalapana,neravuandswaramand attracted resounding applause. Mandapaka Nagalakshmi on mridangam and S. Hanumantharao of on ghatam lent support.
